<div class="page-title">
  <h1>About</h1>
</div>

<div class="about-content">
  <p style="background:#fff8e1; border-left: 3px solid #f0b429; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.9rem;">
    <strong>This site is currently in testing.</strong> Some events may be missing, duplicated, or incorrect whilst we're getting things set up.
  </p>

  <p>
    cov.kids is a community events listing for Coventry and the surrounding area.
    It pulls together gigs, markets, comedy nights, theatre, sport, film screenings,
    and more from a range of local sources - all in one place.
  </p>

  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <p>
    Events are pulled in from Reddit (<a href="https://reddit.com/r/coventry" target="_blank">/r/coventry</a>),
    Eventbrite, venue websites, email newsletters, and <a href="https://cvfolk.co.uk" target="_blank">CVFolk</a>
    - an amazing resource if you're into folk music in the area. A bit of AI and other magic helps extract the details -
    name, date, venue, category - from all that. Everything is then reviewed by a human
    before it appears on the site.
  </p>

  <h2>Inspiration</h2>
  <p>
    Heavily inspired by <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/HadjiChippoSafri" target="_blank">u/HadjiChippoSafri</a>
    on <a href="https://reddit.com/r/coventry" target="_blank">/r/coventry</a>, who has been
    posting weekly "What's On" threads for the community for years.
  </p>

  <h2>Area filters</h2>
  <p>
    By default the site shows events in Coventry itself. Use the <strong>+ Warwickshire</strong> and
    <strong>+ Birmingham</strong> pills to broaden the search to nearby towns (Leamington, Warwick,
    Bedworth, Kenilworth, Nuneaton, Rugby, Stratford…) or to Birmingham gigs. Birmingham listings
    are pretty sparse for now - we're not actively sourcing them yet, but we'll get there.
  </p>

  <h2>Something missing?</h2>
  <p>
    Know of an event or a local listings source we should be picking up?
    Get in touch and we'll add it.
  </p>

  <h2>Got a flyer?</h2>
  <p>
    Spotted something on a poster or received a flyer? Forward it to
    <a href="mailto:ck@kev.cc">ck@kev.cc</a> and we'll try to get it on.
  </p>

  <h2>Run a venue?</h2>
  <p>
    Add <a href="mailto:ck@kev.cc">ck@kev.cc</a> to your venue's mailing list and it should
    start pulling in your events automatically. 🤞
  </p>
</div>
